1
00:00:00,800 --> 00:00:03,623
Two ghosts walk into the stadium tonight.

2
00:00:03,673 --> 00:00:06,497
One has haunted Argentina's matches since nineteen seventy-eight.

3
00:00:06,547 --> 00:00:09,370
The other has blessed Algeria's since independence.

4
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:13,620
Tonight... they finally meet.

5
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:20,905
In episode five, we predicted the kings would survive Morocco, one-nil.

6
00:00:20,955 --> 00:00:25,360
Tonight — the champion of everything... against the nation football betrayed.

7
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:31,405
Welcome back to WorldCup twenty-six Legends, episode six. Argentina versus Algeria.

8
00:00:31,455 --> 00:00:35,860
Group J. The GOAT's last opening night.

9
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:40,770
And stay with me — because in the eighty-third minute of our story...

10
00:00:40,820 --> 00:00:44,090
something happens that you will want to see twice.

11
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:51,140
First, the wound. Spain, nineteen eighty-two.

12
00:00:51,190 --> 00:00:55,830
Algeria — a debutant — beats mighty West Germany two-one. The world gasps.

13
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:59,997
Three days later, West Germany and Austria walk onto the pitch...

14
00:01:00,047 --> 00:01:03,043
already knowing the one score that saves them both.

15
00:01:03,093 --> 00:01:06,090
Eighty minutes of passing in circles.

16
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:13,880
Algeria — eliminated without kicking a ball. They call it the Disgrace of Gijon.

17
00:01:16,500 --> 00:01:20,100
And here is what nobody remembers: FIFA changed the rules because of it.

18
00:01:20,150 --> 00:01:23,750
Every final group game since nineteen eighty-six kicks off at the same time...

19
00:01:23,800 --> 00:01:27,400
because of what was done to Algeria.

20
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:32,715
Forty-four years later, the wounded nation finally meets football royalty...

21
00:01:32,765 --> 00:01:35,980
on the same stage that betrayed them.

22
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:41,970
And what royalty. The world champions. The kings of everything.

23
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:48,225
Lionel Messi. Thirty-nine in this story.

24
00:01:48,275 --> 00:01:52,000
The greatest who ever lived — wrapping the armband for his very last World Cup dance.

25
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:57,753
Julian Alvarez, the Spider, who hunts in packs.

26
00:01:57,803 --> 00:02:00,957
Enzo and Mac Allister, the engine room of champions. And Dibu Martinez...

27
00:02:01,007 --> 00:02:04,160
the wolf in the goalmouth.

28
00:02:06,500 --> 00:02:09,560
They have touched heaven. Tonight they defend it.

29
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:17,515
But Algeria did not come to bow.

30
00:02:17,565 --> 00:02:21,080
This is their golden generation — and they carry nineteen eighty-two in their blood.

31
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:26,560
Riyad Mahrez — the desert fox.

32
00:02:26,610 --> 00:02:29,670
He conquered the Premier League with Leicester, ruled Europe with City...

33
00:02:29,720 --> 00:02:32,780
then chose the desert over the throne.

34
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:38,295
Ismael Bennacer, the tiny metronome of Milan, ninety percent passing in his bones.

35
00:02:38,345 --> 00:02:43,140
And Amine Gouiri — silk and hunger in one body.

36
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:46,950
Forty-four years of waiting walks onto the pitch tonight.

37
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:53,645
And the duel of duels: Messi against Mahrez. The GOAT against the Fox.

38
00:02:53,695 --> 00:02:57,840
Two left feet... that both bend the laws of physics.

39
00:03:00,500 --> 00:03:04,120
Our prediction — built on Gijon, on champions' steel, and on one wolf in the goalmouth.

40
00:03:04,170 --> 00:03:07,790
Watch closely.

41
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:12,905
Fifty-second minute. Enzo finds the Spider — Alvarez spins — finishes. One-nil.

42
00:03:12,955 --> 00:03:17,360
The champions breathe.

43
00:03:17,900 --> 00:03:21,675
But Algeria does not break. They wait. They remember. And the clock crawls toward...

44
00:03:21,725 --> 00:03:25,500
the eighty-third minute.

45
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:31,310
Here it is. The moment we promised. Mahrez. Right flank.

46
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:35,670
He cuts inside — the move every defender knows is coming... and nobody can stop.

47
00:03:38,500 --> 00:03:42,810
The curl rises... dips... the whole stadium stops breathing —

48
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:47,665
DIBU! Fingertips! Off the post!

49
00:03:47,715 --> 00:03:50,380
The wolf of the goalmouth swallows the desert's last spell!

50
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:57,405
Full time in our story: one-nil Argentina.

51
00:03:57,455 --> 00:04:01,860
But Mahrez walks off to applause from BOTH ends. Some wounds heal... with respect.

52
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:06,530
Do you agree? Comment GOAT if Argentina go back-to-back.

53
00:04:06,580 --> 00:04:09,610
Comment FOX if Algeria shocks Group J.

54
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:16,970
And the two ghosts?

55
00:04:17,020 --> 00:04:21,490
Legends six and seven — El Abuelo de la Bombonera, seen at every Argentina match since seventy-eight...

56
00:04:21,540 --> 00:04:26,010
and Le Vieux Fennec, whose raised cane has blessed Algeria since independence.

57
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:30,290
Tonight they watched together. Collect them BOTH inside the game.

58
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:35,680
Which brings us to YOU.

59
00:04:35,730 --> 00:04:38,910
At WorldCup twenty-six dot world, pick three of the forty-eight nations — and every goal they score...

60
00:04:38,960 --> 00:04:42,140
scores for you.

61
00:04:43,900 --> 00:04:49,230
Free to play. Live leaderboard. Underdogs pay triple. Your picks change everything.

62
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:53,560
Hit like — send this to the friend who says Messi is finished.

63
00:04:53,610 --> 00:04:56,970
And subscribe: the legends are only beginning.

